	<tr>
		
			<td bgcolor="#DEDACB">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Proon is indeed the father of Broon, the child cyclops usually found wading in the river. When Broon is slain, commonly his older brother Droon immediately runs towards you from the mountains nearest you and attacks. However, rarely their father named Proon will spawn and be the one to greet you instead of big brother Droon. Rumors that both Droon and Proon can spawn at the same time are just that, rumors, and I cannot confirm them as I have not seen it myself.<BR>
<BR>
Proon is definitely a tough cookie, being a level 42 cyclops he is near the ferocity of a Seafury Cyclops found in the Ocean of Tears. However, in fact I have confirmed that he is at times level 42, I do agree that his level can range from 41 to to 43 but am uncertain.<BR>
<BR>
A level 50 shaman can solo Proon, as well I would suspect that a level 50 necro/druid can as well. Perhaps you do not necessarily need to be of level 50 to accomplish the task of slaying father Proon, but you will need to be near it. Just be careful, since most people mistake him for Droon even though there is a bit of a size difference.<BR>
<BR>
Orinwarf<BR>
Erollisi Marr
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
